title: What is not an end product of photosynthesis? - Quora

response.answer_text: Dear Anonymous, This is a rather open-ended question. Are you sure your teacher didn’t give you a list to choose from when he set your homework? Anyhow, here’s a short list of correct answers: Cheese, capybaras, gold, the Andromeda Galaxy, my left nostril, wombat poo (did you know it come out in cubes!), Carbon Dioxide, The Marianas Trench, Donald Trump. I hope that helps.

What is not an end product of photosynthesis? This is hilarious … this anonymous seeker of insights forgot to add the multiple choices that the teacher originally attached to his/her homework question! Short answer: Almost everything is not produced by photosynthesis! Score another notch for Quora to ban anonymous questions!

Oxygen! Oxygen is a byproduct of the photosynthetic process, it comes from the photooxidation of water. Water is solely used as an electron source to produce NADPH, the reducing power that plants use to reduce carbon dioxide to glucose. Energy for the process comes from the sunlight or artificial visible light .
